text: Mospyne (, ) is a city of district significance in the Proletarskyi District of the Donetsk municipality, Donetsk Oblast (province) of Ukraine. Population: . Population in 2001 was 11,736. Since 2014, the city has been under the control of the self-decleard Donetsk People's Republic. ==Demographics== Native language as of the Ukrainian Census of 2001: *Russian 93.47% *Ukrainian 6.35% ==References== Category:Cities in Donetsk Oblast Category:Donetsk Category:Cities of district significance in Ukraine Category:Populated places established in the Russian Empire
